  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the \"must read\" books one must go through before getting married?",
  "response": "Preparing for marriage can be greatly enhanced by gaining insights from a variety of perspectives on relationships, communication, and partnership. Here are some \"must-read\" books that many people find helpful before tying the knot:\n\n1. **\"The Seven Principles for Making Marriage Work\" by John Gottman and Nan Silver** - This book offers practical advice based on extensive research and emphasizes key principles for fostering a successful marriage.\n\n2. **\"Hold Me Tight: Seven Conversations for a Lifetime of Love\" by Dr. Sue Johnson** - This book introduces Emotionally Focused Therapy (EFT) and provides strategies for creating a secure and loving bond between partners.\n\n3. **\"Attached: The New Science of Adult Attachment\" by Amir Levine and Rachel Heller** - This book explains attachment theory and how understanding personal attachment styles can improve relationship dynamics.\n\n4. **\"The 5 Love Languages: How to Express Heartfelt Commitment to Your Mate\" by Gary Chapman** - Chapman identifies five distinct ways that people express and receive love, helping couples understand each other's needs better.\n\n5. **\"Men Are from Mars, Women Are from Venus\" by John Gray** - This classic explores the differences in communication and emotional needs between genders, providing insights for effective interactions.\n\n6. **\"The Meaning of Marriage: Facing the Complexities of Commitment with the Wisdom of God\" by Timothy Keller** - Keller offers a Christian perspective on marriage, blending theological insights with practical advice.\n\n7. **\"Mating in Captivity: Unlocking Erotic Intelligence\" by Esther Perel** - This book delves into the dynamics of intimacy and desire in long-term relationships, encouraging couples to explore their sexual relationship.\n\n8. **\"Crucial Conversations: Tools for Talking When Stakes Are High\" by Kerry Patterson, Joseph Grenny, Ron McMillan, and Al Switzler** - This book provides tools to navigate difficult conversations, a vital skill for any marriage.\n\n9. **\"The Conscious Marriage: Using the Wisdom of the Heart to Find Your Greatest Love\" by Harville Hendrix** - Hendrix emphasizes the importance of conscious choices in nurturing a lasting and fulfilling marriage.\n\n10. **\"His Needs, Her Needs: Building an Affair-Proof Marriage\" by Willard F. Harley Jr.** - Harley discusses the different emotional needs of husbands and wives, offering insights to strengthen mutual satisfaction in the relationship.\n\nEach of these books offers valuable knowledge and practical advice that can contribute to a healthier, more understanding, and supportive marriage. Reading together and discussing the insights can also deepen your connection before making your vows.",
